PART 3 — Benchmark results (POST /api/statement-runs, warm-cache discipline)
------------------------------------------------------------------
strategy=NATIVE_SQL, limitAccounts=20000, period=2025-03:
  Run 1 (cold): {"runId":21,"strategy":"NATIVE_SQL","accounts":20000,"statementsWritten":20000,"elapsedMs":4314,"statementsPerSec":4636.068613815484,"jdbcQueryCount":3}
  Run 2 (warm): {"runId":22,"strategy":"NATIVE_SQL","accounts":20000,"statementsWritten":20000,"elapsedMs":2071,"statementsPerSec":9657.170449058425,"jdbcQueryCount":3}

strategy=NATIVE_SQL, limitAccounts=200000 (the full account table), period=2025-03:
  Run 1 (cold): {"runId":23,"strategy":"NATIVE_SQL","accounts":200000,"statementsWritten":200000,"elapsedMs":11386,"statementsPerSec":17565.43123133673,"jdbcQueryCount":3}
  Run 2 (warm): {"runId":24,"strategy":"NATIVE_SQL","accounts":200000,"statementsWritten":200000,"elapsedMs":9602,"statementsPerSec":20828.99395959175,"jdbcQueryCount":3}

Coverage note: NATIVE_SQL wrote a statement for every requested account
(20000/20000, 200000/200000) — a real, measured difference from
FETCH_JOIN/BATCHED's ~66.5% coverage at the same limitAccounts (M4/M7). Cause:
PLAN.md's own SQL joins account to transaction unconditionally (no period
filter in the JOIN), then scopes the period entirely inside each FILTER
clause — every account with ANY transaction ever (in this seed, all of them)
gets a row, with correctly zeroed aggregates where nothing matches. This
matches NAIVE's full-coverage semantics, not FETCH_JOIN/BATCHED's inner-join
semantics — see PERFORMANCE.md SS6 and DECISIONS.md D8/D11.

Correctness cross-check (account 123456, run 24):
  SELECT statement_run_id, account_id, total_debits, total_credits, closing_balance, document_ref
  FROM statement WHERE account_id = 123456 AND statement_run_id = 24;

   statement_run_id | account_id | total_debits | total_credits | closing_balance |  document_ref
  ------------------+------------+--------------+---------------+-----------------+----------------
                 24 |     123456 |     -8810.27 |       6378.92 |       -18497.42 | stmt-24-123456

  Matches the running-balance endpoint's last row for the same account/period
  exactly (runningBalance -18497.42 on the last transaction, 2025-03-18).
  total_debits -8810.27 = the lone March debit (2025-03-16); total_credits
  6378.92 = 1796.15 + 4582.77 (the two March credits).

