Both plans use idx_transaction_account_date (M5, V3) — the composite index
built for a completely different investigation (M5's per-account date-range
lookup) turns out to also be exactly the right index for M8's per-account
aggregation and window function, since both are fundamentally "look up one
account's transactions, optionally by date." No new index was needed.
